# Hospital CRM Multi-Agent System

## 1. Overview of the Project Idea

This project implements a **Customer Relationship Management (CRM) multi-agent AI system** designed specifically for hospitals to enhance patient care, operational efficiency, and patient satisfaction. The system leverages coordinated AI agents to manage various aspects of patient relationships, from historical data review to risk assessment and follow-up communication.

### Core Purpose
The system centralizes patient management by deploying specialized AI agents that collaborate through an orchestrator to provide comprehensive healthcare relationship management. Each agent handles a distinct domain while working together to deliver personalized, timely, and compliant patient care experiences.

### Key Benefits
- **Personalized patient care** through historical data analysis and risk assessment
- **Improved patient loyalty** via database-connected loyalty tracking
- **Enhanced follow-up compliance** with automated reminders and scheduling
- **Performance evaluation** through satisfaction and compliance monitoring
- **Risk mitigation** with severity and urgency calculations
- **Centralized coordination** ensuring seamless agent collaboration

